postcontent:
Up for sale is a Savage Axis .308 bolt action rifle. I used this rifle about 4-5 times over the past 2 years I've had it. It is still is great condition and functions flawlessly. This rifle comes with a Bushnell (3-9x40) waterproof scope and a tilting/pivoting bi-pod. It is very accurate and has a nice trigger pull, I can put together 1.5 MOA groupings at 100 yards quite easily. I recently bought a different caliber hunting rifle, so everything I have for this rifle (including ammo) is being packaged up and sold.

Including everything mentioned above, this package also includes 680 rounds of .308 ammo. Almost all the ammo is brass cased, although a few boxes are steel cased soft point. There is plenty of high end hunting ammo mixed in this bunch as well. There is easily $450 in just ammo alone, assuming about .65/round, which is pretty much impossible to find these days. All the ammo was purchased within the last 12 mths.

Price for the whole package is $600. This is extremely fair and is priced to sell, therefore the price is firm. I am not in a hurry to sell so lowball offers will be discarded with no response. Will not separate, package deal only. Must be at least 18 yrs. old and have a valid Ohio ID to purchase, NO EXCEPTIONS!!! FTF sales only, no shipping. CCW owners preferred (like myself). Willing to meet in, or around, the Akron area. 

Although I'm not looking for any trades, feel free to try me. Please don't ask me what I want or what I'm willing to trade for. If you have something you want to trade, let me know what it is exactly, and I will politely accept or decline.

A voice-com adapter may be placed over the front voice-mitter to amplify the user's voice. title: For Sale:  Colt 1911
postcontent: Pachmayr Custom Signature Model Colt MK IV Series 70 Semi-auto pistol in caliber .45ACP. This is a fairly rare Frank Pachmayr accurized Colt 1911, probably done in the 1970's. Features include a new bushing housing at the front of the slide that replaces the factory unit and in addition to the new front sight, also houses a unique Messerschmidt type self aligning bearing, which serves as the new bushing for the matched barrel. The rear end of the barrel to slide lockup is accomplished by a square link and a fitted pin, which gives a broad "foot" of support and assists in a solid lockup of the barrel lugs and hood. Also secured to the frame via the fitted link is the patented slide guide. The lower rails of the slide are beveled to a 45 degree angle and fitted to the beveled upper edges of the guide. Another patented modification is a unique headspace take-up device, which is essentially a spring loaded plunger mounted above the firing pin hole. The plunger presses against the cartridge head when in battery and ensures uniform headspace from cartridge to cartridge. An adjustable Smith & Wesson rear sight has been milled into the slide. The trigger has an adjustable overtravel stop installed. The slide is engraved "Pachmayr Signature Model" on the right side filled in white and the Pachmayr trademark is stamped just below the serial number on the right side of the frame. The slide guide is marked "Pachmayr ACCURIZED Los Angeles U.S.A." on the left side.
